{"build_type":"library","description":"The multi-service supervisor event loop, zero sleeps. Reuses a poll array (ctx slot 3): slot 0 watches the shared signalfd (ctx 0), slots 1..count watch each service timer, slot count+1 watches the control listen socket (ctx 4). Blocks in poll timeout minus one. If signalfd readable: reap dead children and reschedule. Restart any service whose backoff timer fired. If the control socket is readable: accept and answer a status query. Then tail-recurse. ctx: signalfd 0, count 1, table 2, pollbuf 3, control_fd 4.","module_name":"dispatch-multiple-daemon-supervision-events-perpetually","package_name":"dispatch-multiple-daemon-supervision-events-perpetually","function_definitions":{"dispatch-multiple-daemon-supervision-events-perpetually":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"ctx","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"negone","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"lite